RECIPE to run PhotonAnalysisUtils under release 15.3.0.1
======================================================


* configure athena for release 15.3.0.1 production patch


* check out Trigger/TrigAnalysis/TrigObjectMatching tag TrigObjectMatching-00-00-09:
	
	cmt co -r TrigObjectMatching-00-00-09 Trigger/TrigAnalysis/TrigObjectMatching
	cd Trigger/TrigAnalysis/TrigObjectMatching/cmt
	make
	cd -

* check out HEAD version of PhotonAnalysisUtils and compile:

	cmt co PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils
	cd PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/cmt
	make
	cd -

* check out Reconstruction/egamma/egammaPIDTools tag egammaPIDTools-00-00-60

	cmt co -r egammaPIDTools-00-00-60 Reconstruction/egamma/egammaPIDTools
	cd Reconstruction/egamma/egammaPIDTools/cmt
	make 
	cd -

* ... and be optimistic: Run! 

	mkdir run
	cp PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/share/*.py run
	cp PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/share/*.root run
	cp PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/share/*.txt run
	cp PhysicsAnalysis/StandardModelPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/share/*.dat run
	cd run
	ln -s <your-favourite-AOD> AOD.pool.root
	athena.py PAUanalysis_jobOptions-15.3.0.1.py

===> NOTE: PAUanalysis_jobOptions.py is set up to perform photon recovery with official tool, 
           and NO trigger access. Change the options at your need, in the beginning of this
           file


